{"title_page": "Olivier V\u00e9ran", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{short description|French politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name          = Olivier V\u00e9ran\n| image         = Olivier V\u00e9ran - Juillet 2012.jpg\n| office        = [[Minister of Health (France)|Minister of Solidarity and Health]]\n| president     = \n| primeminister = [[\u00c9douard Philippe]]\n| term_start    = 16 February 2020\n| term_end      = \n| predecessor   = [[Agn\u00e8s Buzyn]]\n| successor     = \n| office2       = Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]]<br>for [[Is\u00e8re]]'s [[Is\u00e8re's 1st constituency|1st]] constituency\n| term_start2   = 21 June 2017\n| term_end2     = 16 February 2020\n| predecessor2  = [[Genevi\u00e8ve Fioraso]]\n| successor2    = Camille Galliard-Minier\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1980|04|22|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Saint-Martin-d'H\u00e8res]], [[France]]\n| nationality   = French\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| party         = [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]] {{small|(since 2017)}}\n| spouse        = \n| parents       = \n| children      = \n| education     = [[Joseph Fourier University]] <br> [[Sciences Po]]\n}}\n'''Olivier V\u00e9ran''' (born 22 April 1980) is a French neurologist and politician serving as [[Minister of Health (France)|Minister of Solidarity and Health]] in the [[Second Philippe government|government]] of [[Prime Minister of France|Prime Minister]] [[\u00c9douard Philippe]] since 2020. A member of [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]] (REM), he previously was the member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]] for the [[Is\u00e8re's 1st constituency|first constituency]] of the [[Is\u00e8re]] [[Departments of France|department]] from 2017 until 2020.\n\n== Professional career ==\nV\u00e9ran worked as a neurologist at the Grenoble-Alpes University Hospital. He has served as president of the Association of Hospital Assistants in [[Grenoble]], spokesperson for the National Intersyncal of Hospital Interns, and advisor to the Departmental Order of Physicians of [[Is\u00e8re]].\n\n== Political career ==\nV\u00e9ran was first elected to the National Assembly in the [[2012 French legislative election|2012 elections]], as a member of the [[Socialist Party (France)|Socialist Party]].<ref>[http://www.francetvinfo.fr/elections/resultats/isere_38/isere_1ere-circonscription]{{dead link|date=September 2019}}</ref> During his time in parliament, he was mandated by [[Prime Minister of France|Prime Minister]] [[Jean-Marc Ayrault]] with a government inquiry into the regulatory framework for [[blood product]]s.<ref>Denis Cosnard (July 17, 2013), [https://www.lemonde.fr/economie/article/2013/07/17/sang-une-taxe-en-vue-pour-freiner-les-produits-etrangers_3448813_3234.html Sang : une taxe en vue pour freiner les produits \u00e9trangers] ''[[Le Monde]]''.</ref>\n\nIn 2015, V\u00e9ran resigned as an MP to compete in the [[2015 French departmental elections|2015 departmental elections]] where he became a member of the [[regional council of Auvergne-Rh\u00f4ne-Alpes]]. In 2016, the [[Minister of Health (France)|Minister of Health]] [[Marisol Touraine]] appointed him to steer a committee in charge of drafting reform proposals for France's [[Health care in France|hospital financing]].<ref>Fran\u00e7ois B\u00e9guin (May 25, 2016), [https://www.lemonde.fr/societe/article/2016/05/25/le-gouvernement-veut-revoir-les-regles-de-l-hopital-entreprise_4926106_3224.html Le gouvernement veut revoir les r\u00e8gles de \u00ab l\u2019h\u00f4pital entreprise \u00bb] ''[[Le Monde]]''.</ref>\n\nAhead of the [[2017 French presidential election|2017 presidential election]], V\u00e9ran endorsed [[Emmanuel Macron]] and joined [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]].<ref>Nathalie Raulin (April 20, 2016), [https://www.liberation.fr/france/2016/04/20/en-marche-le-bebe-du-ministre-fait-ses-premiers-pas_1447557 \u00abEn marche\u00bb : le b\u00e9b\u00e9 du ministre fait ses premiers pas] ''[[Lib\u00e9ration]]''.</ref> He was re-elected to the [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]] on 18 June 2017, representing the [[Departments of France|department]] of [[Is\u00e8re]]. In parliament, he served as a member of the Committee on Social Affairs Committee, where he was the [[rapporteur]] on [[Social security in France|social security]] and the government's pension reform plans.<ref>Isabelle Ficek (16 January 2020), [https://www.lesechos.fr/politique-societe/politique/retraites-les-deputes-de-la-majorite-qui-vont-porter-le-projet-de-loi-a-lassemblee-1163512 Retraites : les d\u00e9put\u00e9s de la majorit\u00e9 qui vont porter le projet de loi \u00e0 l'Assembl\u00e9e] ''[[Les \u00c9chos (France)|Les \u00c9chos]]''.</ref>\n\nV\u00e9ran has been Minister for Solidarity and Health since 16 February 2020.<ref>{{cite news | language = fr | url = https://www.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2020/02/16/elections-municipales-a-paris-agnes-buzyn-designee-candidate-lrm-en-remplacement-de-benjamin-griveaux_6029773_823448.html | work= Le Monde | title = Elections municipales \u00e0 Paris : Agn\u00e8s Buzyn d\u00e9sign\u00e9e candidate LRM en remplacement de Benjamin Griveaux | access-date = 5 March 2020 | date= 16 February 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nV\u00e9ran is in a relationship with fellow politician [[Coralie Dubost]].<ref>Fran\u00e7ois B\u00e9guin and Solenn de Royer (March 23, 2020), [https://www.lemonde.fr/sante/article/2020/03/23/coronavirus-au-ministere-de-la-sante-olivier-veran-un-ambitieux-inconnu-propulse-visage-de-la-crise-sanitaire_6034068_1651302.html Coronavirus : au minist\u00e8re de la sant\u00e9, Olivier V\u00e9ran, un ambitieux \u00ab inconnu \u00bb propuls\u00e9 visage de la crise sanitaire]\u00a0''[[Le Monde]]''.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:V\u00e9ran, Olivier}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French Ministers of Health]]\n[[Category:Deputies of the 15th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic]]\n[[Category:La R\u00e9publique En Marche politicians]]\n[[Category:Regional councillors of Auvergne-Rh\u00f4ne-Alpes]]\n[[Category:French neurologists]]\n[[Category:People from Saint-Martin-d'H\u00e8res]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Auvergne-Rh\u00f4ne-Alpes]]\n[[Category:Universit\u00e9 Grenoble Alpes alumni]]\n[[Category:Sciences Po alumni]]\n\n{{France-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{short description|French politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name          = Olivier V\u00e9ran\n| image         = Olivier V\u00e9ran - Juillet 2012.jpg\n| office        = [[Minister of Health (France)|Minister of Solidarity and Health]]\n| president     = \n| primeminister = [[\u00c9douard Philippe]]\n| term_start    = 16 February 2020\n| term_end      = \n| predecessor   = [[Agn\u00e8s Buzyn]]\n| successor     = \n| office2       = Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]]<br>for [[Is\u00e8re]]'s [[Is\u00e8re's 1st constituency|1st]] constituency\n| term_start2   = 21 June 2017\n| term_end2     = 16 February 2020\n| predecessor2  = [[Genevi\u00e8ve Fioraso]]\n| successor2    = Camille Galliard-Minier\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1980|04|22|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Saint-Martin-d'H\u00e8res]], [[France]]\n| nationality   = French\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| party         = [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]] {{small|(since 2017)}}\n| spouse        = \n| parents       = \n| children      = \n| education     = [[Joseph Fourier University]] <br> [[Sciences Po]]\n}}\n'''Olivier V\u00e9ran''' (born 22 April 1980) is a French neurologist and politician serving as [[Minister of Health (France)|Minister of Solidarity and Health]] in the [[Second Philippe government|government]] of [[Prime Minister of France|Prime Minister]] [[\u00c9douard Philippe]] since 2020. A member of [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]] (REM), he previously was the member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]] for the [[Is\u00e8re's 1st constituency|first constituency]] of the [[Is\u00e8re]] [[Departments of France|department]] from 2017 until 2020.\n\n== Professional career ==\nV\u00e9ran worked as a neurologist at the Grenoble-Alpes University Hospital. He has served as president of the Association of Hospital Assistants in [[Grenoble]], spokesperson for the National Intersyncal of Hospital Interns, and advisor to the Departmental Order of Physicians of [[Is\u00e8re]].\n\n== Political career ==\nV\u00e9ran was first elected to the National Assembly in the [[2012 French legislative election|2012 elections]], as a member of the [[Socialist Party (France)|Socialist Party]].<ref>[http://www.francetvinfo.fr/elections/resultats/isere_38/isere_1ere-circonscription]{{dead link|date=September 2019}}</ref> During his time in parliament, he was mandated by [[Prime Minister of France|Prime Minister]] [[Jean-Marc Ayrault]] with a government inquiry into the regulatory framework for [[blood product]]s.<ref>Denis Cosnard (July 17, 2013), [https://www.lemonde.fr/economie/article/2013/07/17/sang-une-taxe-en-vue-pour-freiner-les-produits-etrangers_3448813_3234.html Sang : une taxe en vue pour freiner les produits \u00e9trangers] ''[[Le Monde]]''.</ref>\n\nIn 2015, V\u00e9ran resigned as an MP to compete in the [[2015 French departmental elections|2015 departmental elections]] where he became a member of the [[regional council of Auvergne-Rh\u00f4ne-Alpes]]. In 2016, the [[Minister of Health (France)|Minister of Health]] [[Marisol Touraine]] appointed him to steer a committee in charge of drafting reform proposals for France's [[Health care in France|hospital financing]].<ref>Fran\u00e7ois B\u00e9guin (May 25, 2016), [https://www.lemonde.fr/societe/article/2016/05/25/le-gouvernement-veut-revoir-les-regles-de-l-hopital-entreprise_4926106_3224.html Le gouvernement veut revoir les r\u00e8gles de \u00ab l\u2019h\u00f4pital entreprise \u00bb] ''[[Le Monde]]''.</ref>\n\nAhead of the [[2017 French presidential election|2017 presidential election]], V\u00e9ran endorsed [[Emmanuel Macron]] and joined [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]].<ref>Nathalie Raulin (April 20, 2016), [https://www.liberation.fr/france/2016/04/20/en-marche-le-bebe-du-ministre-fait-ses-premiers-pas_1447557 \u00abEn marche\u00bb : le b\u00e9b\u00e9 du ministre fait ses premiers pas] ''[[Lib\u00e9ration]]''.</ref> He was re-elected to the [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]] on 18 June 2017, representing the [[Departments of France|department]] of [[Is\u00e8re]]. In parliament, he served as a member of the Committee on Social Affairs Committee, where he was the [[rapporteur]] on [[Social security in France|social security]] and the government's pension reform plans.<ref>Isabelle Ficek (16 January 2020), [https://www.lesechos.fr/politique-societe/politique/retraites-les-deputes-de-la-majorite-qui-vont-porter-le-projet-de-loi-a-lassemblee-1163512 Retraites : les d\u00e9put\u00e9s de la majorit\u00e9 qui vont porter le projet de loi \u00e0 l'Assembl\u00e9e] ''[[Les \u00c9chos]]''.</ref>\n\nV\u00e9ran has been Minister for Solidarity and Health since 16 February 2020.<ref>{{cite news | language = fr | url = https://www.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2020/02/16/elections-municipales-a-paris-agnes-buzyn-designee-candidate-lrm-en-remplacement-de-benjamin-griveaux_6029773_823448.html | work= Le Monde | title = Elections municipales \u00e0 Paris : Agn\u00e8s Buzyn d\u00e9sign\u00e9e candidate LRM en remplacement de Benjamin Griveaux | access-date = 5 March 2020 | date= 16 February 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nV\u00e9ran is in a relationship with fellow politician [[Coralie Dubost]].<ref>Fran\u00e7ois B\u00e9guin and Solenn de Royer (March 23, 2020), [https://www.lemonde.fr/sante/article/2020/03/23/coronavirus-au-ministere-de-la-sante-olivier-veran-un-ambitieux-inconnu-propulse-visage-de-la-crise-sanitaire_6034068_1651302.html Coronavirus : au minist\u00e8re de la sant\u00e9, Olivier V\u00e9ran, un ambitieux \u00ab inconnu \u00bb propuls\u00e9 visage de la crise sanitaire]\u00a0''[[Le Monde]]''.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:V\u00e9ran, Olivier}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French Ministers of Health]]\n[[Category:Deputies of the 15th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic]]\n[[Category:La R\u00e9publique En Marche politicians]]\n[[Category:Regional councillors of Auvergne-Rh\u00f4ne-Alpes]]\n[[Category:French neurologists]]\n[[Category:People from Saint-Martin-d'H\u00e8res]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Auvergne-Rh\u00f4ne-Alpes]]\n[[Category:Universit\u00e9 Grenoble Alpes alumni]]\n[[Category:Sciences Po alumni]]\n\n{{France-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toLes Echos(link changed toLes \u00c9chos (France)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olivier_V%C3%A9ran"}
{"title_page": "Corinne Vignon", "text_new": "{{short description|French politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{infobox Politician\n| name        = Corinne Vignon\n| image       = Corinne Vignon, D\u00e9put\u00e9e de Haute-Garonne.jpg\n| office      = Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]]<br>for [[Haute-Garonne's 3rd constituency]]\n| term_start  = 21 June 2017\n| term_end    =\n| predecessor = Laurence Arribag\u00e9\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1963|06|10|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Agen]], France\n| nationality = French\n| party       = [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]]\n}}\n'''Corinne Vignon''' (born 10 June 1963) is a French politician of [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]] (LREM) who has been serving as a member of the [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]] since the [[2017 French legislative election|2017 elections]], representing the [[Haute-Garonne's 3rd constituency|3rd constituency]] of [[Haute-Garonne]].<ref name=\"Bio\">{{Cite web|url=http://elections.interieur.gouv.fr/legislatives-2017/031/03103.html |title=Elections l\u00e9gislatives 2017 |accessdate=19 June 2017 |work=Ministry of the Interior |language=French}}</ref>\n\nIn parliament, Vignon serves on the Committee on Social Affairs.<ref>[http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/deputes/fiche/OMC_PA719512 Corinne Vignon] [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]].</ref> She also chairs of an cross-party working group on pension reform.<ref>Mireille Weinberg (3 April 2019), [https://www.lopinion.fr/edition/economie/corinne-vignon-lrem-retraite-a-62-ans-double-discours-l-executif-est-183049 Corinne Vignon (LREM): \u00abSur la retraite \u00e0 62 ans, le double discours de l\u2019ex\u00e9cutif est impossible \u00e0 tenir\u00bb] ''[[L'Opinion]]''.</ref> Since 2020, she has been serving as her parliamentary group's [[rapporteur|co-rapporteur]] on the government's pension reform plans, alongside [[Guillaume Gouffier-Cha]], [[Jacques Maire]]\u00a0and [[Carole Grandjean]].<ref>Isabelle Ficek (16 January 2020), [https://www.lesechos.fr/politique-societe/politique/retraites-les-deputes-de-la-majorite-qui-vont-porter-le-projet-de-loi-a-lassemblee-1163512 Retraites : les d\u00e9put\u00e9s de la majorit\u00e9 qui vont porter le projet de loi \u00e0 l'Assembl\u00e9e] ''[[Les \u00c9chos (France)|Les \u00c9chos]]''.</ref>\n\nIn addition to her committee assignments, Vignon is a member of the French-Mexican Parliamentary Friendship Group.<ref>[http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/deputes/fiche/OMC_PA719512 Corinne Vignon] [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]].</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2017 French legislative election]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vignon, Corinne}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Deputies of the 15th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic]]\n[[Category:La R\u00e9publique En Marche politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century French women politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Agen]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Nouvelle-Aquitaine]]\n[[Category:Women members of the National Assembly (France)]]\n\n{{France-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{infobox Politician\n| name        = Corinne Vignon\n| image       = Corinne Vignon, D\u00e9put\u00e9e de Haute-Garonne.jpg\n| office      = Member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]]<br>for [[Haute-Garonne's 3rd constituency]]\n| term_start  = 21 June 2017\n| term_end    =\n| predecessor = Laurence Arribag\u00e9\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1963|06|10|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Agen]], France\n| nationality = French\n| party       = [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]]\n}}\n'''Corinne Vignon''' (born 10 June 1963) is a French politician of [[La R\u00e9publique En Marche!]] (LREM) who has been serving as a member of the [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]] since the [[2017 French legislative election|2017 elections]], representing the [[Haute-Garonne's 3rd constituency|3rd constituency]] of [[Haute-Garonne]].<ref name=\"Bio\">{{Cite web|url=http://elections.interieur.gouv.fr/legislatives-2017/031/03103.html |title=Elections l\u00e9gislatives 2017 |accessdate=19 June 2017 |work=Ministry of the Interior |language=French}}</ref>\n\nIn parliament, Vignon serves on the Committee on Social Affairs.<ref>[http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/deputes/fiche/OMC_PA719512 Corinne Vignon] [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]].</ref> She also chairs of an cross-party working group on pension reform.<ref>Mireille Weinberg (3 April 2019), [https://www.lopinion.fr/edition/economie/corinne-vignon-lrem-retraite-a-62-ans-double-discours-l-executif-est-183049 Corinne Vignon (LREM): \u00abSur la retraite \u00e0 62 ans, le double discours de l\u2019ex\u00e9cutif est impossible \u00e0 tenir\u00bb] ''[[L'Opinion]]''.</ref> Since 2020, she has been serving as her parliamentary group's [[rapporteur|co-rapporteur]] on the government's pension reform plans, alongside [[Guillaume Gouffier-Cha]], [[Jacques Maire]]\u00a0and [[Carole Grandjean]].<ref>Isabelle Ficek (16 January 2020), [https://www.lesechos.fr/politique-societe/politique/retraites-les-deputes-de-la-majorite-qui-vont-porter-le-projet-de-loi-a-lassemblee-1163512 Retraites : les d\u00e9put\u00e9s de la majorit\u00e9 qui vont porter le projet de loi \u00e0 l'Assembl\u00e9e] ''[[Les \u00c9chos]]''.</ref>\n\nIn addition to her committee assignments, Vignon is a member of the French-Mexican Parliamentary Friendship Group.<ref>[http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/deputes/fiche/OMC_PA719512 Corinne Vignon] [[National Assembly (France)|French National Assembly]].</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2017 French legislative election]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vignon, Corinne}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[