{"title_page": "List of districts in Malaysia", "text_new": "{{short description|list of administration units of Malaysia}}\n{{about|districts in Malaysia for the purpose of land administration and revenue|local government purpose|List of local governments in Malaysia|electoral purpose|List of Malaysian electoral districts}}\n{{EngvarB|date=January 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox subdivision type\n| name=      ''Daerah'' (District)\n| alt_name=  ''Jajahan'' (Collectivity) ([[Kelantan]])\n| alt_name1= ''Bahagian'' (Division) ([[Sabah]] and [[Sarawak]])\n| alt_name2=\n| alt_name3=\n| alt_name4=\n    \n| map=         Malaysia location map with districts.svg     \n| category=   Second-level [[administrative division]]     \n| territory=  [[States of Malaysia|States]] of [[Malaysia]]\n| upper_unit=\n     \n| start_date=\n| start_date1=\n| start_date2=\n| start_date3=\n| start_date4=\n| legislation_begin=\n| legislation_begin1=\n| legislation_begin2=\n| legislation_begin3=\n| legislation_begin4=\n| legislation_end=\n| legislation_end1=\n| legislation_end2=\n| legislation_end3=\n| legislation_end4=\n| end_date=\n| end_date1=\n| end_date2=\n| end_date3=\n| end_date4=\n\n| current_number= 162<br>87 with 3 cities (Peninsular)<br>28 (Sabah)<br>43 (Sarawak)<br>1 city (Labuan)\n\n| number_date=2020\n\n| type=\n| type1=\n| type2=\n| type3=\n| type4=\n| status=\n| status1=\n| status2=\n| status3=\n| status4=\n| exofficio=\n| exofficio1=\n| exofficio2=\n| exofficio3=\n| exofficio4=\n\n| population_range= Greatest: [[Petaling District]], [[Selangor]]\u20141,812,633 (2010)<br>Least: [[Pakan District]], [[Sarawak]]\u201415,480 (2010)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sarawak.gov.my/web/home/article_view/240/175/|title=The Official Portal of the Sarawak Government|website=www.sarawak.gov.my}}</ref>\n| area_range= Largest: [[Kapit Division]], [[Sarawak]]\u2014{{convert|38,934|km2|abbr=on}}<br>Smallest: [[Putatan District]], [[Sabah]]\u2014{{convert|29.7|km2|abbr=on}}\n\n| government=  City hall, city council, municipal council, district council (in all states and [[Kuala Lumpur]])\n| government1= Corporation (in [[Labuan]] and [[Putrajaya]])\n| government2= \n| government3= Town board (in [[Kudat]], [[Sabah]])\n| government4= Development authority (in [[Bintulu]], [[Sarawak]])\n\n| subdivision=  ''Mukim'' (Townships)\n| subdivision1= ''Daerah'' (District) ([[Kelantan]], [[Sabah]] and [[Sarawak]])\n| subdivision2=\n| subdivision3=\n| subdivision4=   \n }}\n{{Location map many | Malaysia West\n| relief   = yes\n| width    = 250\n| caption  = Districts in West Malaysia\n| lat1_deg = 3.136\n| lon1_deg = 101.688\n| label1   = [[Kuala Lumpur]]\n}}\n{{Location map many | Malaysia East\n| relief   = yes\n| width    = 250\n| caption  = Districts in East Malaysia\n| lat1_deg = 5.971\n| lon1_deg = 116.095\n| label1   = [[Kota Kinabalu]]\n| lat2_deg = 1.553\n| lon2_deg = 110.359\n| label2   = [[Kuching]]\n}}\n'''District''' ([[Malay language|Malay]]: ''[[Daerah]]''; ''[[Jajahan]]'' in [[Kelantan]] and ''[[Divisions of Malaysia|Bahagian]]'' in [[Sabah]] and [[Sarawak]]) is a type of [[administrative division]] below the [[States and federal territories of Malaysia|state]] level in [[Malaysia]]. An administrative district is administered by lands and district office which is headed by district officer.\n\nIn [[Peninsular Malaysia]], a district is a subdivision of a [[States of Malaysia|state]]. A ''[[mukim]]'' is a subdivision of a district. The mukim is however of less importance with respect to the administration of land.\n\nIn [[East Malaysia]], a district is a subdivision of a [[Divisions of Malaysia|division]] of a state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.statoids.com/ymy.html |title=Malaysia Districts |publisher=Statoids.com |date= |accessdate=3 November 2010}}</ref> For example, [[Tuaran District|Tuaran]] is a district within the [[West Coast Division]] of [[Sabah]]. A district is usually named after the main town or its administrative [[Capital (political)|capital]]; for example, the town of [[Sandakan]] is the capital of the Sandakan District, as well as the capital of [[Sandakan Division]]. In [[Sarawak]], some districts are further divided into sub-districts (''daerah kecil''; literally \"small district\") before the mukim level, while [[Sabah]] are not divided into mukim.\n\nAn administrative district can be distinguished from a [[Local government in Malaysia|local government]] area where the former deals with land administration and revenue while the latter deals with the planning and delivery of basic infrastructure to its inhabitants. Administrative district boundaries are usually coextensive with local government area boundaries but may sometimes differ especially in urbanised areas. For example, the local government of [[Petaling District]] in [[Selangor]] are administrated by [[Petaling Jaya City Council]], [[Shah Alam City Council]] and [[Subang Jaya Municipal Council]]; or even the local government of both [[Northeast Penang Island District]] and [[Southwest Penang Island District]] in [[Penang]] are administrated by [[City Council of Penang Island|Penang Island City Council]]. The below is a list of districts in Malaysia.\n\n==By states==\n{{Malaysia statehood dates}}\n\n===West Malaysia===\n{{legend|#FFAAAA|[[Federal Territories (Malaysia)|Federal Territory (Not District)]]}}\n{{legend|#AAFFAA|City-status District}}\n{{legend|#AAAAFF|Municipal-status District}}\n{| class=\"wikitable unsortable\"\n|-\n!Federal Territory/State\n!District Name\n!Capital/Largest settlement\n!Local Government\n!Population (2010{{My10}})<!--Include Non-Malaysian-->\n!Area (km\u00b2)\n!Density\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#fff;\"| {{flag|Federal Territory (Malaysia)}}\n|- style=\"background:#faa;\"\n|{{N/A}}\n| {{flag|Kuala Lumpur}}\n|[[Kuala Lumpur City Hall|Kuala Lumpur H]]\n|{{pop density|1674621|243|km2|disp=table|prec=1}}\n|- style=\"background:#faa;\"\n|{{N/A}}\n| {{flag|Putrajaya}}\n|[[Putrajaya Corporation|Putrajaya P]]\n|{{pop density|72413|49|km2|disp=table|prec=1}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"11\" colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#fff;\"| {{flag|Johor}}\n|- style=\"background:#aaf;\"\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of Batu Pahat, Johor.svg}} [[Batu Pahat District]]\n|[[Batu Pahat (town)|Batu Pahat]]\n|[[Batu Pahat Municipal Council|Batu Pahat M]]<br>[[Yong Peng District Council|Yong Peng D]]\n|{{pop density|417458|1873|km2|disp=table|prec=1}}\n|- style=\"background:#afa;\"\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of Johor Bahru, Johor.svg}} [[Johor Bahru District]]\n|[[Johor Bahru]]\n|[[Johor Bahru City Council|Johor Bahru C]]<br>[[Iskandar Puteri City Council|Iskandar Puteri C]]<br>[[Pasir Gudang Municipal Council|Pasir Gudang M]]\n|{{pop density|1386569|1064|km2|disp=table|prec=1}}\n|- style=\"background:#aaf;\"\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of Kluang, Johor.svg}} [[Kluang District]]\n|[[Kluang (town)|Kluang]]\n|[[Kluang Municipal Council|Kluang M]]<br>[[Simpang Renggam District Council|Simpang Renggam D]]\n|{{pop density|298332|2865|km2|disp=table|prec=1}}\n|-style=\"background:#aaf;\"\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of Kota Tinggi, Johor.svg}} [[Kota Tinggi District]]\n|[[Kota Tinggi]]\n|[[Kota Tinggi District Council|Kota Tinggi D]]<br>[[Pengerang Municipal Council|Pengerang M]]\n|{{pop density|193210|3489|km2|disp=table|prec=1}}\n|- style=\"background:#aaf;\"\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of Kulai, Johor.svg}} [[Kulai District]]\n|[[Kulai]]\n|[[Kulai Municipal Council|Kulai M]]\n|{{pop density|251650|754|km2|disp=table|prec=1}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of Mersing, Johor.svg}} [[Mersing District]]\n|[[Mersing]]\n|[[Mersing District Council|Mersing D]]\n|{{pop density|70894|2838|km2|disp=table|prec=1}}\n|- style=\"background:#aaf;\"\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of Muar, Johor.svg}} [[Muar District]]\n|[[Muar (town)|Muar]]\n|[[Muar Municipal Council|Muar M]]\n|{{pop density|247957|1354|km2|disp=table|prec=1}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of Pontian, Johor.svg}} [[Pontian District]]\n|[[Po