k\nFile:Selangor districts numbered.svg|Districts in Selangor\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[District]]\n* [[List of capitals in Malaysia]]\n* [[List of districts in Malaysia by population]]\n* [[Local government in Malaysia]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Districts of Malaysia}}\n* {{statoids|id=ymy|title=Districts of Malaysia}}\n\n{{Malaysia topics}}\n{{Articles on second-level administrative divisions of Asian countries}}\n{{Districts of Malaysia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Districts in Malaysia}}\n[[Category:Districts of Malaysia| ]]\n[[Category:Subdivisions of Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Lists of subdivisions of Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Country subdivisions in Asia|Malaysia 2, Districts]]\n[[Category:Second-level administrative country subdivisions|Districts, Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Malaysia geography-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|list of administration units of Malaysia}}\n{{about|districts in Malaysia for the purpose of land administration and revenue|local government purpose|List of local governments in Malaysia|electoral purpose|List of Malaysian electoral districts}}\n{{EngvarB|date=January 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox subdivision type\n| name=      ''Daerah'' (District)\n| alt_name=  ''Jajahan'' (Collectivity) ([[Kelantan]])\n| alt_name1= ''Bahagian'' (Division) ([[Sabah]] and [[Sarawak]])\n| alt_name2=\n| alt_name3=\n| alt_name4=\n    \n| map=         Malaysia location map with districts.svg     \n| category=   Second-level [[administrative division]]     \n| territory=  [[States of Malaysia|States]] of [[Malaysia]]\n| upper_unit=\n     \n| start_date=\n| start_date1=\n| start_date2=\n| start_date3=\n| start_date4=\n| legislation_begin=\n| legislation_begin1=\n| legislation_begin2=\n| legislation_begin3=\n| legislation_begin4=\n| legislation_end=\n| legislation_end1=\n| legislation_end2=\n| legislation_end3=\n| legislation_end4=\n| end_date=\n| end_date1=\n| end_date2=\n| end_