rahan-municipal-council-effective-today/|title=It's Kota Samarahan Municipal Council effective today|author=Lian Cheng|publisher=The Borneo Post|date=11 November 2016|accessdate=19 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mpks.sarawak.gov.my/pengenalan.php|title=Laman Web Rasmi Majlis Daerah Samarahan|website=www.mpks.sarawak.gov.my}}</ref>\n|87923\n|-\n|[[Simunjan District]]\n|[[Simunjan District|Simunjan]]\n|[[Simunjan District Council|Simunjan D]]\n|39226\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[Sarikei Division|Sarikei]]\n|[[Julau District]]\n|[[Julau]]\n|[[Meradong and Julau District Council|Meradong and Julau D]]\n|15816\n|-\n|[[Meradong District]]\n|[[Bintangor, Sarawak|Bintangor]]\n|[[Meradong and Julau District Council|Meradong and Julau D]]\n|29441\n|-\n|[[Pakan District]]\n|[[Pakan, Sarawak|Pakan]]\n|[[Meradong and Julau District Council|Meradong and Julau D]]\n|15480\n|-\n|[[Sarikei District]]\n|[[Sarikei]]\n|[[Sarikei District Council|Sarikei D]]\n|58021\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Serian Division|Serian]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theborneopost.com/2015/04/12/serian-now-a-division/|title=Serian now a division|author=Samuel Aubrey|publisher=The Borneo Post|date=12 April 2015|accessdate=15 May 2015}}</ref>\n|[[Serian District]]\n|[[Serian, Sarawak|Serian]]\n|[[Serian District Council|Serian D]]\n|91599\n|-\n|[[Tebedu District]]\n|[[Tebedu]]\n|[[Serian District Council|Serian D]]\n|{{N/A}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Sibu Division|Sibu]]\n|[[Kanowit District]]\n|[[Kanowit]]\n|[[Kanowit District Council|Kanowit D]]\n|28954\n|- style=\"background:#aaf;\"\n|[[Sibu District]]\n|[[Sibu]]\n|[[Sibu Municipal Council|Sibu D]]<hr>[[Sibu Rural District Council|Sibu Rural D (Sibu Jaya)]]\n|247995\n|-\n|[[Selangau District]]\n|[[Selangau]]\n|[[Sibu Rural District Council|Sibu Rural D]]\n|22819\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Sri Aman Division|Sri Aman]]\n|[[Lubok Antu District]]\n|[[Lubok Antu]]\n|[[Lubok Antu District Council|Lubok Antu D]]\n|27984\n|-\n|[[Sri Aman District]]\n|[[Simanggang]]\n|[[Sri Aman District Council|Sri Aman D]]\n|66790\n|}\n\n==Townships (Mukim)==\nIn the 11 states of the [[Peninsular Malaysia]] including the [[Federal Territories (Malaysia)|Federal Territories]], there are townships (precint for Putrajaya) that been administered by the district office and also the [[State governments of Malaysia|state government]]. For a list, see [[:Category:Mukims of Malaysia]].\n\n==Gallery==\n===Labelled maps===\n<center>\n{{Johor Labelled Map}}\n{{-}}\n{{Pahang Labelled Map|width=350}}\n{{-}}\n{{Penang district level labelled map|width=350}}\n{{-}}\n{{Sabah Labelled Map}}\n{{-}}\n{{Terengganu Labelled Map}}\n{{-}}\n{{Perak Labelled Map}}\n</center>\n\n===Maps===\n<gallery>\nFile:Districts of Johor.PNG|Districts in Johor\nFile:Districts in Perak.svg|Districts in Perak\nFile:Selangor districts numbered.svg|Districts in Selangor\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[District]]\n* [[List of capitals in Malaysia]]\n* [[List of districts in Malaysia by population]]\n* [[Local government in Malaysia]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Districts of Malaysia}}\n* {{statoids|id=ymy|title=Districts of Malaysia}}\n\n{{Malaysia topics}}\n{{Articles on second-level administrative divisions of Asian countries}}\n{{Districts of Malaysia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Districts in Malaysia}}\n[[Category:Districts of Malaysia| ]]\n[[Category:Subdivisions of Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Lists of subdivisions of Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Country subdivisions in Asia|Malaysia 2, Districts]]\n[[Category:Second-level administrative country subdivisions|Districts, Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Malaysia geography-related lists]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toSimanggang(link changed toSri Aman) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_districts_in_Malaysia"}
